laboratory_examinations.findings: WBC count: 13.0 K/uL (normal range: 4.0 - 11.0 K/uL), elevated.

Mild dependent bibasilar atelectasis, no abnormalities in liver, gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, and adrenals. Kidneys show normal contrast uptake without hydronephrosis. Tiny subcentimeter hypodensities bilaterally. No pathologic lymphadenopathy, free air, or free fluid.
